{#
  Shared "header + 3-card grid" layout for every internal-link discovery
  section on the site. This is the canonical UI for any section whose
  job is to say "here are N related pages you should read next" —
  briefings rails on tool pages, "More on this sector" on a blog post,
  surname-cluster siblings on a sanctions profile, "Other S&P 500
  companies in this sector" on a company profile, and so on.

  Why this layout (and why it is centralised):
    • Reader UX: scannable card grid beats a bullet list with dotted
      separators, especially once the list has more than 2-3 items.
      The canonical example is the "Saab Moran cluster — 3 dossiers
      sharing this surname" block on /research/sdn/; that card grid
      predates this macro and established the visual language.
    • Internal-linking SEO: a single shared component means every
      "related pages" section has identical structural markup, so when
      we tighten anchor-text conventions or add schema (ItemList /
      BreadcrumbList) we do it in one place, not 10.
    • Consistency: before this macro existed, every page hand-rolled
      its own <ul class="related"> with slightly different CSS and
      copy. The 2026-04 design audit flagged that drift as both an
      aesthetic problem and a crawl-signal problem.

  Inputs for card_grid_section():
      heading      : str   — H2 text for the section
      meta         : str   — optional right-aligned meta text in the header
                             (e.g. "3 dossiers sharing this surname")
      intro        : str   — optional paragraph under the header
      cards        : list  — list of dicts, each with:
                               href      (required, str)
                               title     (required, str)
                               eyebrow   (optional, str) — red-dot label
                               raw       (optional, str) — mono secondary line
                               tagline   (optional, str) — short descriptor
                               meta_rows (optional, list[str/HTML])
                               cta       (optional, str, default "Read more")
      aria_label   : str   — accessible section label
      footer_link  : dict  — {"href": ..., "label": ...} browse CTA below grid
      max_cards    : int  — max visible cards (default 3). Remaining items
                             are reachable only via footer_link.
      footer_mode  : str  — "auto" (default): show footer only when
                             len(cards) > max_cards AND footer_link is set.
                             "always": show footer whenever footer_link is set
                             (use when the browse target is a full index with
                             more than this section could ever list, e.g.
                             /briefing). "never": never show footer.

  CSS lives in templates/_base.html.j2 under the .cr-card-* namespace,
  so every page that extends _base.html.j2 inherits the look — no per-
  page style duplication required.
#}
{% macro card_grid_section(heading, meta=None, intro=None, cards=None, aria_label=None, footer_link=None, max_cards=3, footer_mode='auto') -%}
{%- set _all = cards or [] %}
{%- set _cap = max_cards|int %}
{%- set _total = _all|length %}
{%- set _cards = _all[:_cap] %}
{%- set _show_footer = footer_link and (footer_mode == 'always' or (footer_mode == 'auto' and _total > _cap)) %}
{%- if _cards %}
<section class="cr-card-section"{% if aria_label %} aria-label="{{ aria_label }}"{% endif %}>
  <header class="cr-card-header">
    <h2 class="cr-card-title">{{ heading }}</h2>
    {% if meta %}<span class="cr-card-meta">{{ meta }}</span>{% endif %}
  </header>
  {% if intro %}<p class="cr-card-intro">{{ intro }}</p>{% endif %}
  <div class="cr-card-grid">
    {% for c in _cards %}
    <a class="cr-card" href="{{ c.href }}">
      {% if c.eyebrow %}<span class="cr-card-eyebrow">{{ c.eyebrow }}</span>{% endif %}
      <h3 class="cr-card-headline">{{ c.title }}</h3>
      {% if c.raw %}<span class="cr-card-raw">{{ c.raw }}</span>{% endif %}
      {% if c.tagline %}<p class="cr-card-tagline">{{ c.tagline }}</p>{% endif %}
      {% if c.meta_rows %}
      <div class="cr-card-meta-rows">
        {% for m in c.meta_rows %}<span>{{ m|safe }}</span>{% endfor %}
      </div>
      {% endif %}
      <span class="cr-card-cta">{{ c.cta|default('Read more') }}</span>
    </a>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
  {% if _show_footer %}
  <p class="cr-card-footer">
    <a href="{{ footer_link.href }}"><strong>{{ footer_link.label }}</strong></a>
  </p>
  {% endif %}
</section>
{%- endif %}
{%- endmacro %}
